Icon.description: Icons are a crucial part of our design system and product experience. They are used to express objects, actions, and ideas visually.

Button.description: An interactive element in various styles that allows users to take actions.

Links.description: A component with button-like properties built to be used in text.

Copy To Clipboard.description: The copy to clipboard component enables the user to copy links, code snippets and more.

CTA Group β.description: As the name suggests CTA Groups are used for adding up to 3 CTAs to forms or dialog-type components.

Flyout Menu.description: Derived from a popover, the flyout menu features drill-down/nested capabilities for menus and lists.Dev equivalent: gux-listbox

Context Menu Button.description: 💡 Figma TipWhen nesting this component into an auto layout (for eg. a list of contacts), make sure to change the canvas stacking to first on top in the advanced auto layout settings.This will prevent the menu being stacked behind other elements.Contextual menus contain a small set of relevant actions, related to a control, a piece of content, a view in an app, or an area of the UI without cluttering the interface.

Form Footer.description: The form footer should always be the last part of a form. This is where the CTAs of the form should reside.

Selector Card.description: Selector cards are used as a supercharged radio/checkbox input, the can hold icons and description to better explain the options the user is selecting.

Textfield.description: A text field is for single-line text input that is short and specific. Examples of these would be names, passwords, and numbers.

Spin Button.description: A two-segment UI control increases or decreases the numeric value in a field incrementally.

Time Picker.description: A component that allows the user to select a specific time.

Textarea.description: A resizable text box for multiple lines of standard text.

Phone Input.description: Phone inputs allow users to enter phone numbers into forms. They may allow the user to select a specific country code.

Multi-Select Dropdown.description: A basic component that provides a list of options in a limited space.

Single-Select Dropdown.description: A basic component that provides a list of options in a limited space.

Date Picker - Range.description: A component that allows users to select a range of dates.

Calendar - Range.description: A pre-designed and pre-build calendar component.

Calendar - Day.description: A pre-designed and pre-build calendar component.

Date Picker - Day.description: A component that allows users to select a single day.

Month Picker.description: A component that allows users to select a month.

Time-Zone Picker.description: Time-zone pickers allow users to change the local time on a UI.

Color Picker.description: A configurable interface for color selection.

Segmented Control.description: Segmented controls are used for changing the visualization of data.

Slider.description: An element that allows for selection of a value within a range.

Checkbox Group Set.description: A basic element that can be marked as selected and can be used in a list to provide multiple selection options.

Checkbox Group Form Field.description: A basic element that can be marked as selected and can be used in a list to provide multiple selection options.

Checkbox Nested Group Set.description: A basic element that can be marked as selected and can be used in a list to provide multiple selection options.

Checkbox.description: A basic element that can be marked as selected and can be used in a list to provide multiple selection options.

Radio Button Group Set.description: Radio buttons are UI elements that select one option from a list of mutually exclusive options.

Radio Button Group Form Field.description: Radio buttons are UI elements that select one option from a list of mutually exclusive options.

Radio Buttons.description: Radio buttons are UI elements that select one option from a list of mutually exclusive options.

Star Rating.description: Simple component that visually shows a rating with the use of star shapes.

Toggle.description: A digital on/off switch that always has a default value and prompts users to choose between two mutually exclusive options.

Search.description: A pre-designed and pre-built component that can be used to implement a search functionality within a user interface.

Add or Change Image β.description: Feature to edit or change the user's avatar photo.

Avatar Group β.description: Avatar groups are a collection of avatars representing multiple users.

Avatar.description: Avatars are graphical representations of users through a profile picture or initials.

Tag.description: A component that allows users to categorize content, display active filters, provide keywords, and/or allow for additional context.

Table Pagination.description: A component that separates out table content into discrete pages.

Table Toolbar.description: A toolbar containing relevant actions related to a table.

Context Menu Cell.description: 💡 Tip: to show the context menu, set the state to active on the Context Menu Button layer.

Prebuilt Table Desktop Fixed Column.description: The table is a collection of related data held in a tabular format consisting of columns and rows.

Prebuilt Table Desktop.description: The table is a collection of related data held in a tabular format consisting of columns and rows.

Accordion.description: A component that allows users to collapse and expand a section of content.

Card.description: Cards are used to group similar concepts together to make a page easier to read.

Breadcrumbs.description: A navigation element that shows the user's current location in the application. It is most clearly seen in the Admin area of Genesys Cloud.

Tab Item.description: A basic component that allows switching between content within one single view.

Tabs Set.description: A basic component that allows switching between content within one single view.

Advanced Tabs Sets.description: A component that allows switching between content within one single view with advanced functionality.

Advanced Tabs Groups.description: A component that allows switching between content within one single view with advanced functionality.

Blank State.description: Blank State component displays when there is no content or data to show in a particular section of the application.

In-Line Alert Banners.description: An in-line alert banner is a non-modal message that is related to objects in a view.

Modal.description: A dialog that appears on top of the main content, disabling it, until the user explicitly interacts with the dialog.

Popover.description: A component that displays persistent content such as menus, options, custom information, and pickers. Popovers float on top of a UI.

Loading Placeholder States.description: Progress and loading indicators express an unspecified wait time or display the length of a process.

Spinner.description: Progress and loading indicators express an unspecified wait time or display the length of a process.

Toast.description: A component that provides temporary notifications that show brief information. It is typically not disruptive unless an immediate action is required.

Tooltip.description: A component that appears on hover which provides additional contextual help or information.

Slot.description: As the name suggests, the slot is just a placeholder for you to insert a component!
